Several languages, especially those of emerging economies, will offer children a better chance of finding a meaningful job.
In Scotland, schools themselves choose which languages they teach.
A number of schools will focus on the more classic modern languages, while other schools will teach languages that are most important to the United Kingdom when they look ahead to 2020, such as the Mandarin or Japanese.
Whatever the interest of your child, there will always be different languages to choose from in independent schools, with teachers specializing in this field.
Scottish independent schools are working to provide a learning environment that prepares children and gives them the skills needed to succeed, regardless of the future.
At present, it cannot be denied that languages in a global business environment remain vital for the future of the country, so this needs to be reflected in education.
Modern languages should actually be regarded as 'international communication skills'.
