The new warship of Germany is being delayed again
The latest frigate of the German Navy should have come into service in 2014 to replace the outdated warships of the Cold War, but it will take at least one year before it is ready, due to faulty systems and rising costs, local media reported.
The launch of the 'Rheinland-Pfalz', the leading ship in the brand new Baden-Wuerttemberg class frigates, has now been postponed until the first half of 2019, according to the newsmagazine Die Zeit that a military spokesman quotes.
